BOM REGRESSION INCIDENT (2026-06-21, /gm-skill user session): gm-plugkit@2.0.1578 (npm latest at the time) shipped a UTF-8 BOM (efbbbf) at the top of bootstrap.js -> `node` SyntaxError 'Invalid or unexpected token' -> `bun x gm-plugkit@latest spool` (the SKILL.md boot command) broke for EVERY user; 2.0.1577 and earlier clean. Root cause: a PowerShell 5.1 edit wrote JS source with the default UTF-16/UTF-8-BOM encoding instead of utf8-no-BOM (the same trap AGENTS.md already warns about for spool bodies, but it bit committed SOURCE files). Three tracked files had the BOM: gm-plugkit/bootstrap.js, gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js, .agents/plugins/marketplace.json. Fix: strip first 3 bytes (tail -c +4), validate node --check / JSON.parse. GUARDRAIL added: test.js checkNoBom() scans git ls-files text exts and fails on any leading efbbbf (Principle 8: structural prevention). HARD RULE: never write a tracked source file with a BOM; on Windows/PowerShell always use -Encoding utf8 (no BOM) or the Write tool, for ALL source files not just spool bodies. Recovery during the incident: pin to 2.0.1577 to get a live watcher since @latest was unbootable.